        <LEXMeaning Id="000937001002000" IsBiblicalTerm="Y" EntryCode="88.159" Indent="0">
          <LEXDomains>
            <LEXDomain>Moral and Ethical Qualities and Related Behavior</LEXDomain>
          </LEXDomains>
          <LEXSubDomains>
            <LEXSubDomain>Mislead, Lead Astray, Deceive</LEXSubDomain>
          </LEXSubDomains>
          <LEXSenses>
            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2021-02-04 23:05:13" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>to deceive a person by devious and crafty means, with the possibility of a religious connotation in view of the literal meaning ‘to bewitch’ (see {D:53.98})</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>to deceive</Gloss>
                <Gloss>to bewitch</Gloss>
                <Gloss>to beguile</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>It is also possible that {L:βασκαίνω&lt;SDBG:βασκαίνω:000000&gt;} in {S:04800300100012} is to be understood literally in the sense of bewitching by means of black magic (see {D:53.98}).</Comments>
            </LEXSense>
          </LEXSenses>
